  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — `apps/crawler`\n\n**Current state: 0% coverage.** No test files exist anywhere in the app (confirmed via `find`). `pytest` is already declared as a dev dependency in `pyproject.toml` but nothing uses it — no `tests/` dir, no `conftest.py`. This is a from-scratch gap analysis across the four source files: `base.py`, `models.py`, `providers.py`, `main.py`.\n\nMocking will be central here since most functions do real network I/O or file I/O via `scrapling`. Recommend a `tests/` dir with a `conftest.py` providing a fake \"page\" object (mimicking `scrapling`'s `.css()/.first/.get_all_text()/.attrib`) and `tmp_path`-based redirection of `DATA_DIR`/`STATE_DIR`/`LOG_DIR`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Pure functions — highest ROI, zero mocking needed\n\n#### `parse_french_date` (base.py:90)\nUntested. Two input formats, accented/non-accented months, unknown months, malformed text.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_dates.py\nimport pytest\nfrom base import parse_french_date\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22 juin 2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"octobre 30, 2017\", \"2017-10-30\"),\n    (\"1 août 2020\", \"2020-08-01\"),      # accented month\n    (\"1 aout 2020\", \"2020-08-01\"),      # non-accented alias\n    (\"3 décembre 2021\", \"2021-12-03\"),\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_valid(text, expected):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) == expected\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text\", [\n    \"\",\n    \"no date here\",\n    \"32 juin 2019\",          # invalid day — should raise or return None?\n    \"22 frobuary 2019\",      # unknown month name\n    \"22 2019\",               # missing month\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_invalid_returns_none(text):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) is None\n```\n**Edge case not covered by current code**: `\"32 juin 2019\"` (out-of-range day) will match the regex but `datetime(...)` will raise `ValueError` uncaught — this is a real gap, not just a missing test. Worth deciding: should `parse_french_date` catch and return `None`, or is an uncaught crash acceptable mid-`parse_article`? Currently `crawl()` catches `Exception` around `parse_article`, so it degrades to \"skip and retry,\" but that's an accidental safety net, not a designed one.\n\n#### `parse_numeric_date` (base.py:107)\n```python\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22/06/2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"22/06/2019 14:30\", \"2019-06-22\"),  # trailing time\n    (\"no slashes\", None),\n    (\"32/13/2019\", None),  # should this raise instead of matching? — same ValueError gap as above\n])\ndef test_parse_numeric_date(text, expected):\n    assert parse_numeric_date(text) == expected\n```\n\n#### `MadagascarTribune._is_article_link` (providers.py:69)\nPure static method, zero coverage.\n```python\n# tests/test_providers_tribune.py\nimport pytest\nfrom providers import MadagascarTribune\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"href,expected\", [\n    (None, False),\n    (\"article-slug.html\", True),\n    (\"category-.html\", False),           # \"-.html\" is the rubrique convention\n    (\"http://external.com/x.html\", False),\n    (\"/absolute/path.html\", False),\n    (\"_AuthorName,42_.html\", False),\n    (\"article-slug.php\", False),         # wrong extension\n])\ndef test_is_article_link(href, expected):\n    assert MadagascarTribune._is_article_link(href) is expected\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `discover_sitemap_urls` / `_fetch_xml` (base.py:48-87) — untested, network-mocked\n\nGaps: sitemap-index recursion, `<image:image><image:loc>` filtering (the exact bug the comment warns about), gzip-sniffed responses, leading-whitespace-before-XML-declaration handling.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_sitemap.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, Mock\nimport gzip\nfrom base import discover_sitemap_urls, _fetch_xml\n\nFLAT_SITEMAP = b\"\"\"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\"\n        xmlns:image=\"http://www.google.com/schemas/sitemap-image/1.1\">\n  <url>\n    <loc>https://example.mg/article-1</loc>\n    <image:image><image:loc>https://example.mg/img1.jpg</image:loc></image:image>\n  </url>\n  <url><loc>https://example.mg/article-2</loc></url>\n</urlset>\"\"\"\n\nINDEX_SITEMAP = b\"\"\"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<sitemapindex xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n  <sitemap><loc>https://example.mg/sub-1.xml</loc></sitemap>\n</sitemapindex>\"\"\"\n\ndef _mock_response(body: bytes):\n    resp = Mock()\n    resp.__enter__ = Mock(return_value=resp)\n    resp.__exit__ = Mock(return_value=False)\n    resp.read = Mock(return_value=body)\n    return resp\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_flat_excludes_image_locs():\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=_mock_response(FLAT_SITEMAP)):\n        urls = list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"https://example.mg/sitemap.xml\"))\n    assert urls == [\"https://example.mg/article-1\", \"https://example.mg/article-2\"]\n    assert \"https://example.mg/img1.jpg\" not in urls  # regression guard for the .iter() bug the comment warns about\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_follows_index_recursively():\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\") as mock_open:\n        mock_open.side_effect = [_mock_response(INDEX_SITEMAP), _mock_response(FLAT_SITEMAP)]\n        urls = list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"https://example.mg/sitemap_index.xml\"))\n    assert urls == [\"https://example.mg/article-1\", \"https://example.mg/article-2\"]\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_decompresses_gzip_despite_content_type():\n    compressed = gzip.compress(FLAT_SITEMAP)\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=_mock_response(compressed)):\n        raw = _fetch_xml(\"https://example.mg/sitemap.xml\")\n    assert raw.startswith(\"<?xml\")\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_strips_leading_whitespace():\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=_mock_response(b\"\\n  \" + FLAT_SITEMAP)):\n        raw = _fetch_xml(\"https://example.mg/sitemap.xml\")\n    assert raw.startswith(\"<?xml\")\n```\n**Missing error handling test**: no coverage for a malformed XML response (`ET.fromstring` raising `ParseError`) — currently unhandled inside the generator, propagates up through `list_article_urls()` into `crawl()`'s outer `except Exception` (marked `\"error: {exc}\"` and re-raised). Worth an explicit test asserting that behavior is intentional.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `NewsSource` core pipeline — the highest-value, currently completely untested surface\n\n#### `crawl()` (base.py:273-333)\nThis is the most important gap — it owns resumability, dedup, checkpointing, and error isolation, and has zero coverage. Needs a fake subclass.\n\n```python\n# tests/conftest.py\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Article, SiteSelectors\nfrom base import NewsSource\n\nclass FakeSource(NewsSource):\n    source_name = \"fake\"\n    selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\")\n\n    def __init__(self, urls, parse_results=None, raise_on=None):\n        self._urls = urls\n        self._parse_results = parse_results or {}\n        self._raise_on = raise_on or {}\n\n    def list_article_urls(self):\n        yield from self._urls\n\n    def parse_article(self, url):\n        if url in self._raise_on:\n            raise self._raise_on[url]\n        return self._parse_results.get(url)  # None simulates \"not an article\"\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef redirect_dirs(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base.DATA_DIR\", tmp_path / \"data\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base.STATE_DIR\", tmp_path / \"state\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base.LOG_DIR\", tmp_path / \"logs\")\n    return tmp_path\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_crawl.py\nfrom models import Article\n\ndef make_article(url):\n    return Article(url=url, title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None,\n                    published_date=None, category=None, source=\"fake\",\n                    scraped_at=\"2026-01-01T00:00:00\")\n\ndef test_crawl_stops_at_limit(redirect_dirs):\n    urls = [f\"https://x/{i}\" for i in range(5)]\n    results = {u: make_article(u) for u in urls}\n    source = FakeSource(urls, parse_results=results)\n    saved = source.crawl(limit=2)\n    assert len(saved) == 2\n    state = source._load_state()\n    assert state[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"limit reached\"\n\ndef test_crawl_unlimited_exhausts_all_urls(redirect_dirs):\n    urls = [f\"https://x/{i}\" for i in range(3)]\n    results = {u: make_article(u) for u in urls}\n    source = FakeSource(urls, parse_results=results)\n    saved = source.crawl(limit=0)\n    assert len(saved) == 3\n    assert source._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"exhausted\"\n\ndef test_crawl_skips_already_seen_urls(redirect_dirs):\n    url = \"https://x/1\"\n    source = FakeSource([url], parse_results={url: make_article(url)})\n    source._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [url], \"total_saved\": 0})\n    saved = source.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert saved == []  # never re-fetched\n\ndef test_crawl_marks_non_article_as_seen_without_saving(redirect_dirs):\n    url = \"https://x/not-an-article\"\n    source = FakeSource([url], parse_results={url: None})\n    saved = source.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert saved == []\n    assert url in source._load_state()[\"seen_urls\"]  # so it's never retried\n\ndef test_crawl_continues_after_parse_error_and_does_not_mark_seen(redirect_dirs):\n    bad, good = \"https://x/bad\", \"https://x/good\"\n    source = FakeSource(\n        [bad, good],\n        parse_results={good: make_article(good)},\n        raise_on={bad: RuntimeError(\"network blip\")},\n    )\n    saved = source.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert [a.url for a in saved] == [good]\n    assert bad not in source._load_state()[\"seen_urls\"]  # retried next run, per the comment's intent\n\ndef test_crawl_discovery_failure_preserves_prior_progress_and_reraises(redirect_dirs):\n    def bad_discovery():\n        yield \"https://x/ok\"\n        raise ConnectionError(\"network cut\")\n    source = FakeSource([])\n    source.list_article_urls = bad_discovery\n    source._parse_results = {\"https://x/ok\": make_article(\"https://x/ok\")}\n    source.parse_article = lambda url: source._parse_results.get(url)\n    with pytest.raises(ConnectionError):\n        source.crawl(limit=10)\n    state = source._load_state()\n    assert state[\"last_stopped_reason\"].startswith(\"error:\")\n    assert \"https://x/ok\" in state[\"seen_urls\"]  # the one article before the crash is intact\n\ndef test_crawl_calls_on_save_callback(redirect_dirs):\n    url = \"https://x/1\"\n    source = FakeSource([url], parse_results={url: make_article(url)})\n    calls = []\n    source.crawl(limit=10, on_save=calls.append)\n    assert len(calls) == 1 and calls[0].url == url\n```\n\n#### `_load_state` / `_save_state` (base.py:138-149)\nNo coverage of the atomic-write path or missing-file default.\n```python\ndef test_load_state_missing_file_returns_default(redirect_dirs):\n    source = FakeSource([])\n    assert source._load_state() == {\"seen_urls\": [], \"total_saved\": 0}\n\ndef test_save_state_is_atomic_no_tmp_file_left_behind(redirect_dirs):\n    source = FakeSource([])\n    source._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [\"a\"], \"total_saved\": 1})\n    assert source._state_path.exists()\n    assert not source._state_path.with_suffix(\".json.tmp\").exists()\n    assert source._load_state()[\"seen_urls\"] == [\"a\"]\n```\n\n#### `_append_article` / `_log` (base.py:151-160)\nUntested; both are simple append-only I/O but worth a smoke test for path creation and JSONL format.\n```python\ndef test_append_article_writes_jsonl_line(redirect_dirs):\n    source = FakeSource([])\n    source._append_article(make_article(\"https://x/1\"))\n    lines = source._data_path.read_text().splitlines()\n    assert len(lines) == 1\n    import json\n    assert json.loads(lines[0])[\"url\"] == \"https://x/1\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `parse_article` and `_extract_images` (base.py:174-271) — the densest untested branch logic\n\nNo coverage at all for HTML-parsing branches: missing title (→ `None`), optional author/date/category presence, three date-format branches (`raw`/`french`/`numeric`), `published_date_attr` vs text-parse path, embed-url iframe-vs-video fallback, `about:blank` iframe skip, image dedup/absolute-URL/`data:` filtering, `data-src` vs `src` precedence.\n\nRequires a fake page fixture mimicking scrapling's API:\n\n```python\n# tests/conftest.py (additions)\nclass FakeElement:\n    def __init__(self, text=\"\", attrib=None):\n        self._text = text\n        self.attrib = attrib or {}\n    def get_all_text(self, strip=True):\n        return self._text.strip() if strip else self._text\n\nclass FakeQuerySet(list):\n    @property\n    def first(self):\n        return self[0] if self else None\n\nclass FakePage:\n    def __init__(self, css_map):\n        self._css_map = css_map  # selector -> list[FakeElement]\n    def css(self, selector):\n        return FakeQuerySet(self._css_map.get(selector, []))\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_parse_article.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom models import SiteSelectors\nfrom base import NewsSource\nfrom tests.conftest import FakePage, FakeElement, FakeSource\n\ndef source_with_page(page, selectors=None):\n    src = FakeSource([])\n    src.selectors = selectors or SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\")\n    src.fetch = lambda url: page\n    return src\n\ndef test_parse_article_returns_none_when_title_missing():\n    page = FakePage({})  # no h1 at all\n    src = source_with_page(page)\n    assert src.parse_article(\"https://x/1\") is None\n\ndef test_parse_article_joins_nonempty_body_paragraphs():\n    page = FakePage({\n        \"h1\": [FakeElement(\"Title\")],\n        \"p\": [FakeElement(\"Para 1\"), FakeElement(\"  \"), FakeElement(\"Para 2\")],\n    })\n    src = source_with_page(page)\n    article = src.parse_article(\"https://x/1\")\n    assert article.body == \"Para 1\\n\\nPara 2\"  # blank paragraph excluded\n\ndef test_parse_article_published_date_attr_path():\n    selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\", published_date=\"time\",\n                               published_date_attr=\"datetime\")\n    page = FakePage({\n        \"h1\": [FakeElement(\"T\")], \"p\": [],\n        \"time\": [FakeElement(attrib={\"datetime\": \"2020-01-01\"})],\n    })\n    src = source_with_page(page, selectors)\n    assert src.parse_article(\"https://x/1\").published_date == \"2020-01-01\"\n\ndef test_parse_article_published_date_french_text_path():\n    selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\", published_date=\"span\",\n                               published_date_format=\"french\")\n    page = FakePage({\"h1\": [FakeElement(\"T\")], \"p\": [], \"span\": [FakeElement(\"22 juin 2019\")]})\n    src = source_with_page(page, selectors)\n    assert src.parse_article(\"https://x/1\").published_date == \"2019-06-22\"\n\ndef test_parse_article_embed_url_prefers_iframe_over_video():\n    page = FakePage({\n        \"h1\": [FakeElement(\"T\")], \"p\": [],\n        \"iframe\": [FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"https://youtube.com/embed/1\"})],\n        \"video source\": [FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"https://x/v.mp4\"})],\n    })\n    src = source_with_page(page)\n    assert src.parse_article(\"https://x/1\").embed_url == \"https://youtube.com/embed/1\"\n\ndef test_parse_article_embed_url_skips_about_blank_iframe():\n    page = FakePage({\n        \"h1\": [FakeElement(\"T\")], \"p\": [],\n        \"iframe\": [FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"about:blank\"})],\n        \"video source\": [FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"https://x/v.mp4\"})],\n    })\n    src = source_with_page(page)\n    assert src.parse_article(\"https://x/1\").embed_url == \"https://x/v.mp4\"\n\ndef test_parse_article_no_embed_when_no_iframe_or_video():\n    page = FakePage({\"h1\": [FakeElement(\"T\")], \"p\": []})\n    src = source_with_page(page)\n    assert src.parse_article(\"https://x/1\").embed_url is None\n```\n\n`_extract_images` in isolation:\n```python\n# tests/test_base_extract_images.py\ndef test_extract_images_dedupes_and_absolutizes():\n    page = FakePage({\n        \"article img, .entry-content img, .td-post-content img, \"\n        \".post-content img, .vcex-post-content img, figure img\": [\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"/relative.jpg\"}),\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"https://x/relative.jpg\"}),  # dupe once absolutized... actually different path, adjust\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"data-src\": \"/lazy.jpg\", \"src\": \"/placeholder.gif\"}),\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"data:image/png;base64,AAAA\"}),  # must be skipped\n        ],\n    })\n    src = FakeSource([])\n    images = src._extract_images(page, \"https://x/article\", cover_image=\"https://x/cover.jpg\")\n    assert images[0] == \"https://x/cover.jpg\"       # cover first\n    assert \"https://x/lazy.jpg\" in images            # data-src preferred over src\n    assert \"https://x/placeholder.gif\" not in images\n    assert not any(u.startswith(\"data:\") for u in images)\n\ndef test_extract_images_empty_when_no_containers_match():\n    page = FakePage({})\n    src = FakeSource([])\n    assert src._extract_images(page, \"https://x/1\", cover_image=None) == []\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Provider-specific crawlers — integration-shaped gaps, all untested\n\nThese have real, nontrivial control flow beyond selector config and are currently 0% covered:\n\n#### `MadagascarTribune.list_article_urls` / `_discover_categories` (providers.py:62-103)\nGaps: pagination stop condition (`new_on_page == 0`), the `_max_pages_per_category` safety cap, redirect-URL tracking (`page.url` reassignment for `debut_articles` continuation).\n```python\n# tests/test_providers_tribune_crawl.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, Mock\nfrom providers import MadagascarTribune\n\ndef fake_page(html, url, links):\n    p = Mock()\n    p.html_content = html\n    p.url = url\n    p.css = Mock(return_value=[Mock(attrib={\"href\": h}) for h in links])\n    return p\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_stops_when_page_has_no_new_links():\n    source = MadagascarTribune()\n    with patch.object(source, \"_discover_categories\", return_value=[\"https://x/rub1\"]), \\\n         patch(\"providers.Fetcher.get\") as mock_get:\n        mock_get.side_effect = [\n            fake_page(\"\", \"https://x/rub1\", [\"a1.html\", \"a2.html\"]),\n            fake_page(\"\", \"https://x/rub1\", []),  # empty page -> stop\n        ]\n        urls = list(source.list_article_urls())\n    assert urls == [\"https://x/a1.html\", \"https://x/a2.html\"]\n    assert mock_get.call_count == 2  # did not walk to _max_pages_per_category\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_respects_max_pages_safety_cap():\n    source = MadagascarTribune()\n    source._max_pages_per_category = 2\n    with patch.object(source, \"_discover_categories\", return_value=[\"https://x/rub1\"]), \\\n         patch(\"providers.Fetcher.get\") as mock_get:\n        mock_get.return_value = fake_page(\"\", \"https://x/rub1\", [\"always-new.html\"])\n        urls = list(source.list_article_urls())\n    assert mock_get.call_count == 2  # capped, even though pages \"never\" go empty\n```\n\n#### `FreeNews.list_article_urls` (providers.py:165-183)\nGaps: WP REST 400-past-last-page termination vs a *different* HTTPError (should propagate), empty-`posts`-list termination, pagination increment.\n```python\n# tests/test_providers_freenews.py\nimport json, urllib.error\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, Mock\nfrom providers import FreeNews\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_stops_on_400_past_last_page():\n    source = FreeNews()\n    resp1 = Mock(); resp1.__enter__ = Mock(return_value=resp1); resp1.__exit__ = Mock(return_value=False)\n    resp1.read = Mock(return_value=json.dumps([{\"link\": \"https://x/1\"}]).encode())\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\") as mock_open:\n        mock_open.side_effect = [\n            resp1,\n            urllib.error.HTTPError(\"url\", 400, \"bad\", {}, None),\n        ]\n        urls = list(source.list_article_urls())\n    assert urls == [\"https://x/1\"]\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_reraises_non_400_http_error():\n    source = FreeNews()\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\") as mock_open:\n        mock_open.side_effect = urllib.error.HTTPError(\"url\", 500, \"server error\", {}, None)\n        with pytest.raises(urllib.error.HTTPError):\n            list(source.list_article_urls())\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_stops_on_empty_posts_list():\n    source = FreeNews()\n    resp = Mock(); resp.__enter__ = Mock(return_value=resp); resp.__exit__ = Mock(return_value=False)\n    resp.read = Mock(return_value=b\"[]\")\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=resp):\n        assert list(source.list_article_urls()) == []\n```\n**Missing error handling test / actual gap**: the `except urllib.error.HTTPError` only catches HTTP-layer failures — a plain `URLError` (DNS failure, timeout) is *not* caught and will propagate out of `list_article_urls()`, through `crawl()`'s outer `try/except`, aborting the whole run rather than just this page. Worth a test asserting that's the intended (if surprising) behavior, or fixing it.\n\n#### `Moov.list_article_urls` (providers.py:204-228)\nGaps: BFS dedup via `queued`, `/article/` substring filter, silent `except Exception: continue` on frontier-expansion fetch failure (an untested behavior that swallows *all* exceptions, not just network ones).\n```python\n# tests/test_providers_moov.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, Mock\nfrom providers import Moov\n\ndef fake_page(links):\n    p = Mock()\n    p.css = Mock(return_value=[Mock(attrib={\"href\": h}) for h in links])\n    return p\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_bfs_dedupes_and_filters_non_article_links():\n    source = Moov()\n    with patch(\"providers.Fetcher.get\") as mock_get:\n        mock_get.side_effect = [\n            fake_page([\"/article/1\", \"/article/2\", \"/not-article/x\"]),  # home\n            fake_page([\"/article/1\", \"/article/3\"]),                    # from /article/1 (1 is a dupe)\n            fake_page([]),                                              # from /article/2\n            fake_page([]),                                              # from /article/3\n        ]\n        urls = list(source.list_article_urls())\n    assert sorted(urls) == sorted([\n        \"https://new.moov.mg/article/1\",\n        \"https://new.moov.mg/article/2\",\n        \"https://new.moov.mg/article/3\",\n    ])\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_continues_frontier_when_a_page_fetch_fails():\n    source = Moov()\n    with patch(\"providers.Fetcher.get\") as mock_get:\n        mock_get.side_effect = [\n            fake_page([\"/article/1\", \"/article/2\"]),\n            RuntimeError(\"fetch failed\"),   # expanding /article/1 fails\n            fake_page([]),                  # /article/2 still expands fine\n        ]\n        urls = list(source.list_article_urls())\n    assert set(urls) == {\"https://new.moov.mg/article/1\", \"https://new.moov.mg/article/2\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `main.py` — CLI entry point, completely untested\n\nGaps: `--limit` default, `provider` choice validation (argparse exits with code 2 on bad choice — untested), the `\"all\"` fan-out loop, `on_save` callback wiring.\n```python\n# tests/test_main.py\nimport sys\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, Mock\nimport pytest\nimport main\n\ndef test_main_invalid_provider_exits_with_usage_error(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"not-a-real-provider\"])\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit) as exc:\n        main.main()\n    assert exc.value.code == 2\n\ndef test_main_all_crawls_every_provider(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"all\", \"--limit\", \"1\"])\n    fake_source = Mock()\n    fake_source.crawl.return_value = []\n    fake_source._data_path = \"data.jsonl\"\n    fake_source._state_path = \"state.json\"\n    fake_source._log_path = \"log.txt\"\n    fake_cls = Mock(return_value=fake_source)\n    with patch.dict(main.PROVIDERS, {\"a\": fake_cls, \"b\": fake_cls}, clear=True):\n        main.main()\n    assert fake_source.crawl.call_count == 2\n    fake_source.crawl.assert_called_with(limit=1, on_save=pytest.approx  # placeholder — replace with ANY matcher\n        if False else fake_source.crawl.call_args.kwargs[\"on_save\"])\n\ndef test_main_default_limit_is_ten(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"a\"])\n    fake_source = Mock(crawl=Mock(return_value=[]))\n    fake_source._data_path = fake_source._state_path = fake_source._log_path = \"x\"\n    with patch.dict(main.PROVIDERS, {\"a\": Mock(return_value=fake_source)}, clear=True):\n        main.main()\n    assert fake_source.crawl.call_args.kwargs[\"limit\"] == 10\n```\n(Note the `test_main_all_crawls_every_provider` assertion line is awkward — simplify in practice to `fake_source.crawl.assert_called_with(limit=1, on_save=ANY)` using `unittest.mock.ANY`.)\n\n---\n\n### 7. `models.py` — low priority but currently zero coverage\n\nOnly worth a smoke test confirming defaults, since it's pure data:\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nfrom models import Article, SiteSelectors\n\ndef test_article_defaults():\n    a = Article(url=\"u\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n    assert a.cover_image is None\n    assert a.embed_url is None\n    assert a.images == []\n\ndef test_article_images_default_not_shared_between_instances():\n    a1 = Article(url=\"1\", title=\"\", body=\"\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                 category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"\")\n    a2 = Article(url=\"2\", title=\"\", body=\"\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                 category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"\")\n    a1.images.append(\"x\")\n    assert a2.images == []  # guards against a `field(default_factory=list)` regression to a mutable default\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of gaps by priority\n\n| Area | File | Priority | Why |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `crawl()` resumability/error-isolation | base.py | **Critical** | Core correctness guarantee (no data loss, no duplicate fetches); zero tests today |\n| `parse_article` branch logic | base.py | **Critical** | Dense conditional logic (date formats, optional fields, embed fallback) feeding every provider |\n| `discover_sitemap_urls` image-loc filtering | base.py | High | Comment explicitly flags a past bug class; needs a regression test |\n| Provider-specific crawlers (Tribune, FreeNews, Moov) | providers.py | High | Each has unique pagination/BFS/termination logic, fully untested |\n| `parse_french_date`/`parse_numeric_date` invalid-input crash | base.py | Medium (bug, not just gap) | Out-of-range day/month raises uncaught `ValueError` instead of returning `None` |\n| `FreeNews` non-400 `URLError` not caught | providers.py | Medium (bug, not just gap) | A transient network error aborts the whole provider run instead of just that page |\n| `main.py` CLI | main.py | Low | Thin wrapper, but zero coverage of `--limit` default and invalid-provider exit code |\n| `models.py` | models.py | Low | Pure dataclasses, smoke-test only |\n\n**Recommended next step**: land `tests/conftest.py` with the `FakeSource`/`FakePage` fixtures shown above, then implement the `crawl()` and `parse_article` test suites first — they cover the two functions every provider depends on and would have caught real bugs (the `ValueError` crash paths) during this analysis alone.\n",
