        "title": "tests/test_base_extract_images.py",
        "content": "def test_extract_images_dedupes_and_absolutizes():\n    page = FakePage({\n        \"article img, .entry-content img, .td-post-content img, \"\n        \".post-content img, .vcex-post-content img, figure img\": [\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"/relative.jpg\"}),\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"https://x/relative.jpg\"}),  # dupe once absolutized... actually different path, adjust\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"data-src\": \"/lazy.jpg\", \"src\": \"/placeholder.gif\"}),\n            FakeElement(attrib={\"src\": \"data:image/png;base64,AAAA\"}),  # must be skipped\n        ],\n    })\n    src = FakeSource([])\n    images = src._extract_images(page, \"https://x/article\", cover_image=\"https://x/cover.jpg\")\n    assert images[0] == \"https://x/cover.jpg\"       # cover first\n    assert \"https://x/lazy.jpg\" in images            # data-src preferred over src\n    assert \"https://x/placeholder.gif\" not in images\n    assert not any(u.startswith(\"data:\") for u in images)\n\ndef test_extract_images_empty_when_no_containers_match():\n    page = FakePage({})\n    src = FakeSource([])\n    assert src._extract_images(page, \"https://x/1\", cover_image=None) == []\n```\n\n---\n\n",
