        "title": "`FreeNews.list_article_urls` (providers.py:165-183)",
        "content": "Gaps: WP REST 400-past-last-page termination vs a *different* HTTPError (should propagate), empty-`posts`-list termination, pagination increment.\n```python\n",
        "level": 4
      },
      {
        "title": "tests/test_providers_freenews.py",
        "content": "import json, urllib.error\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, Mock\nfrom providers import FreeNews\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_stops_on_400_past_last_page():\n    source = FreeNews()\n    resp1 = Mock(); resp1.__enter__ = Mock(return_value=resp1); resp1.__exit__ = Mock(return_value=False)\n    resp1.read = Mock(return_value=json.dumps([{\"link\": \"https://x/1\"}]).encode())\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\") as mock_open:\n        mock_open.side_effect = [\n            resp1,\n            urllib.error.HTTPError(\"url\", 400, \"bad\", {}, None),\n        ]\n        urls = list(source.list_article_urls())\n    assert urls == [\"https://x/1\"]\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_reraises_non_400_http_error():\n    source = FreeNews()\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\") as mock_open:\n        mock_open.side_effect = urllib.error.HTTPError(\"url\", 500, \"server error\", {}, None)\n        with pytest.raises(urllib.error.HTTPError):\n            list(source.list_article_urls())\n\ndef test_list_article_urls_stops_on_empty_posts_list():\n    source = FreeNews()\n    resp = Mock(); resp.__enter__ = Mock(return_value=resp); resp.__exit__ = Mock(return_value=False)\n    resp.read = Mock(return_value=b\"[]\")\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=resp):\n        assert list(source.list_article_urls()) == []\n```\n**Missing error handling test / actual gap**: the `except urllib.error.HTTPError` only catches HTTP-layer failures — a plain `URLError` (DNS failure, timeout) is *not* caught and will propagate out of `list_article_urls()`, through `crawl()`'s outer `try/except`, aborting the whole run rather than just this page. Worth a test asserting that's the intended (if surprising) behavior, or fixing it.\n\n",
        "level": 1
